		<h1 class=border>Hedgehog</h1>
		<img src="https://s8.postimg.org/u50cgnqwl/george-kendall-437242.jpg" alt="Hedgehog">
		<div class="text">
			<p class="interesting background border">Hedgehog spines are actually hollow hairs made stiff with keratin.</p>
			<ul class="list background border">
				<li><span>Diet</span>: Hedgehogs are omnivorous.</li>
                <li><span>Habits</span>: They are mostly nocturnal, and all wild hedgehogs can hibernate.</li>
                <li><span>Lifespan</span>: In the wild, larger species live 4-7 years, and smaller ones live 2-4 years.</li>
                <li><span>Communication</span>: Hedgehogs communicate through grunts, sniffles, and squeals. </li>
			 </ul>
            <p class="final background border">The Hedgehog is a spiny mammal, native to parts of Europe, Asia, and Africa. Their main defense mechanism is rolling into a tight ball, and they have some natural immunity to snake venom.</p>
